  <div class="container">
    <h1>About LeBron James</h1>
    <p>
      LeBron Raymone James Sr., born December 30, 1984, is a professional basketball player for the Los Angeles Lakers.
      Known as "King James", he is the NBA's all-time scoring leader and a four-time NBA champion.
    </p>

    <details>
      <summary>üìñ Early Life</summary>
      <p>
        LeBron Raymone James was born on December 30, 1984, in Akron, Ohio. He was raised by his mother, Gloria James, who had him when she was just 16 years old. Life was tough growing up ‚Äî they moved around a lot and often struggled financially.

Despite the hardships, LeBron found support from people in his community. One of the most important figures was Frank Walker, a local youth football coach who took LeBron in when his mother decided he needed a more stable home. Frank also introduced him to basketball when LeBron was just 9 years old.

From there, LeBron‚Äôs talent grew fast. He played AAU basketball with close friends who would later become known as the "Fab Four", and together they all went to St. Vincent‚ÄìSt. Mary High School. LeBron quickly became a basketball sensation in high school ‚Äî his games were even nationally televised, which was rare at the time.

By the time he graduated, he was already being called "The Chosen One" and was on the cover of Sports Illustrated. He skipped college and went straight to the NBA draft in 2003, where he was picked #1 overall by the Cleveland Cavaliers ‚Äî beginning one of the most legendary basketball careers of all time.
      </p>
      <img src="https://www.si.com/.image/t_share/MTY4MTI4MDkzODc0MzAwMTc3/lebron-james-childhoodjpg.jpg" width="200" height="200" alt="LeBron childhood">
    </details>

    <details>
      <summary>üèÄ NBA Career</summary>
      <p>
        LeBron James's NBA career is a testament to sustained excellence, adaptability, and a relentless pursuit of greatness. Over more than two decades, he has not only achieved remarkable individual success but has also significantly impacted every team he has been part of.

Cleveland Cavaliers (2003‚Äì2010; 2014‚Äì2018): LeBron was drafted first overall by the Cavaliers in 2003. In his initial stint, he rapidly became the team's cornerstone, leading them to their first NBA Finals appearance in 2007. After a four-year tenure with the Miami Heat, he returned to Cleveland in 2014. In 2016, he led the Cavaliers to their first-ever NBA championship, overcoming a 3‚Äì1 deficit against the Golden State Warriors in the Finals. 
en.wikipedia.org

Miami Heat (2010‚Äì2014): LeBron's move to Miami marked a new chapter, where he joined forces with Dwyane Wade and Chris Bosh. During his four seasons with the Heat, he reached the NBA Finals each year, securing back-to-back championships in 2012 and 2013. His performance during this period solidified his reputation as one of the game's elite players.

Los Angeles Lakers (2018‚Äìpresent): In 2018, LeBron signed with the Lakers, aiming to restore the franchise's glory. His leadership culminated in the 2020 NBA championship, where he was named Finals MVP, making him the first player to earn this honor with three different teams.

Throughout his career, LeBron has amassed numerous accolades, including four NBA championships, four MVP awards, and 20 All-Star selections. In 2023, he became the NBA's all-time leading scorer, surpassing Kareem Abdul-Jabbar. His longevity and consistent performance have set new standards in professional basketball.
en.wikipedia.org

In 2024, LeBron and his son Bronny made history by becoming the first father-son duo to play together in an NBA game. The following year, he was inducted into the Naismith Memorial Basketball Hall of Fame as a member of the 2008 U.S. Olympic "Redeem Team." 
en.wikipedia.org

LeBron James's career is not just defined by statistics and championships but also by his influence on the game and his ability to inspire both teammates and fans alike.









Sources


      </p>
      <img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/7a/LeBron_James_%2851959977144%29_%28cropped2%29.jpg/960px-LeBron_James_%2851959977144%29_%28cropped2%29.jpg" width="200" height="200" alt="LeBron">
      <p>
        LeBron has made 10 NBA Finals appearances, winning 4 titles, and was a key player in each team's success.
      </p>
    </details>

